    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1831_04_24_page01.jpg"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#North-Audley-Street-1_ENK"/>1 North Audley Street
                        <date when="1831-04-24">April 24<hi rend="superscript"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> 1831</date></dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    You would oblige still<lb/>
                    more than you have <choice><orig>al<lb/>
                    ready</orig><reg>already</reg></choice> obliged me by <choice><orig>let<lb/>
                    ting</orig><reg>letting</reg></choice> me know what I<lb/>
                    am in your debt or in<lb/>
                    some body else's for the<lb/>
                    books you were so kind<lb/>
                    to procure for me to send<lb/>
                    over to my nieces at <choice><orig>Flo-<lb/>
                    rence</orig><reg>Florence</reg></choice> -. Pray write one<lb/>
                    line by 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. post to let me<lb/>
                    know because the time<lb/>
                    for my going hence <choice><orig>ap-<lb/>
                    proaches</orig><reg>approaches</reg></choice> &amp; I should be sorry<lb/>
                    to depart in pounds &amp; <choice><orig>shil-<lb/>
                    ling</orig><reg>shilling</reg></choice> &amp; pence debt, while<lb/>
                    all debts of gratitude I<lb/>
                    am glad to remain <del><unclear></unclear></del><lb/> 
                    <add>under</add><lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1831_04_24_page01.jpg"/>
                    under without feeling<lb/>
                    them any weight<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HersX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Herschel</persName> sent<lb/>
                    me a book which he<lb/>
                    thinks is out of print<lb/>
                    &amp; which I have not been<lb/>
                    able to find - Perhaps<lb/>
                    you with your great<lb/>
                    means &amp; great good will<lb/>
                    could find it for me<lb/>
                    Title -<lb/>
                    <title ref="./Workography.xml#Thirt1">Thirty letters on<lb/>
                    Various subjects</title><lb/>
                    by<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#JackW1">William Jackson</persName><lb/>
                    (3<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> <choice><orig>Ed<hi rend="superscript">n</hi></orig><reg>Edition</reg></choice> with considerable<lb/>
                    additions<lb/>
                    Printed for <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CadeT2">T Cadell</persName> <unclear><choice><orig>Jun</orig><reg>Junior</reg></choice></unclear><lb/>
                    &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DaviW1">W <choice><orig>Davis</orig><reg>Davies</reg></choice></persName> <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Strand_ENK">Strand</placeName><lb/>
                    1795<lb/>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1831_04_24_page03.jpg"/>
                    With Compliments to<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MurrJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Murray</persName> I am<lb/>
                    <choice><orig>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.</orig><reg>Dear</reg></choice> Sir<lb/>
                    Your obliged<lb/>
                    humble <choice><orig>Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></orig><reg>Servant</reg></choice><lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        My youngest brother<lb/>
                        <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM2">Pakenham</persName> who I<lb/>
                        believe was at the<lb/>
                        Charter house with you<lb/>
                        is going to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Kolkata_IN">Calcutta</placeName><note>Calcutta was known as Calcutta until 2001, when it was renamed as Kolkata.</note><lb/>
                        in a few days -<lb/>
                        Have you any <hi rend="underline">command</hi><lb/>
                        there that he can execute<lb/>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
        <back> </back>
    </text>
